  rect(inset: 12pt)[Determine the order of each of the elements of the dihedral group $D_8.$ ]
)
Since $ 
    D_8 &= angle.l r, s bar r^4 = s^2  = e, r s = s r^(-1) angle.r \ 
    & = {e , r, r^2, r^3, s, r s, r^2 s, r^3 s}.
$ 
Using 
$ 
   | r^k | = n/(gcd(n, k)) = 4/(gcd(4, k)), 
$ 
and the fact that any reflection $r^k s$ is of order 2, since  $ 
     (r^(k) s)^2 = r^k s r^k s = r^k r^(-k) s^2 = e, 
$ 
we have: $ 
    |e| = 1, \ 
    |r| = 4, med |r^2 | = 2, med |r^3| = 4, \ 
    |s| = | r s | = | r^2 s | = | r^3 s | = 2. 
$ 

