- An octahedron has 6 vertices, from which we label from 1 to 6. 
  A rigid motion in G sents vertex 1 to six possible locations. Afterwhich, there are four possible locations for vertex 2, and then the location of the remaining four vertices are determined. Thus, by the multiplication principle, $|G| = 6 times 4 = 24.$

